parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission pump can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Whining or loud noise from the transmission
transmission slipping or hesitation
vehicle losing power or stalling
RPMs revving high
check engine light or warning lights illuminated
transmission fluid leak or low pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling or losing power
transmission slipping or hesitation
RPMs revving high
check engine light or warning lights illuminated
transmission fluid leak or low pressure
vehicle unable to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train can cause the vehicle to lose motive power, increasing the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Vehicle stalling or losing power
transmission slipping or hesitation
RPMs revving high
check engine light or warning lights illuminated
transmission fluid leak or low pressure
vehicle unable to shift gears.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the sliding door actuator can cause the door to stick shut or not latch properly, posing a safety risk to passengers, especially in emergency situations.
symptoms: The sliding door makes a buzzing noise
the door does not latch or unlock properly
the door tries to close repeatedly
the door alarm sounds while the vehicle is stationary
the door may even open on its own while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while driving, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off while driving
the instrument panel and display screen go blank
the vehicle seizes in park
the gear shifter cannot shift gears
the headlights and other electrical components malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch and transmission can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the vehicle shuts off while driving
the transmission dies and needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Battery Drain and Electrical Component Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery and electrical components can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off, leading to a loss of power steering and brakes, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The battery drains quickly
the vehicle shuts off while driving
the electrical components malfunction
the headlights and other lights flicker or go out.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the active headrest can cause it to deploy unexpectedly, potentially leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities. The sudden deployment can also cause distractions while driving, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The headrest deploys suddenly without any collision or impact
often with a loud noise or force
and cannot be reset to its original position. In some cases
the headrest may hit the driver or passenger in the head or neck
causing injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of headrest components, such as plastic clips or metal rods, can cause the headrest to malfunction or deploy unexpectedly, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The headrest may suddenly deploy or break apart
often with a loud noise or force
and cannot be reset to its original position. In some cases
the headrest may be stuck in a forward position
causing discomfort or distraction while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The uncommanded deployment of the airbag can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the driver or passenger is not expecting it.
symptoms: The airbag deploys suddenly without any collision or impact
often with a loud noise or force
and can cause injuries or distractions while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Active Head Restraint (AHR) can cause the headrest to deploy unexpectedly, potentially leading to injuries or accidents, especially if it happens while driving.
symptoms: The headrest deploys or explodes without warning
hitting the driver or passenger in the head or neck
causing injuries or discomfort. The headrest may also become stuck in the deployed position
making it difficult to reset or repair.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The illumination of the airbag light can indicate a faulty airbag system, which can lead to unexpected deployments or failures to deploy in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The airbag light on the dashboard illuminates
indicating a problem with the airbag system. The light may stay on constantly or flash intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt can lead to injuries or fatalities in the event of an accident, especially if the airbags do not deploy.
symptoms: The seat belt locks up or fails to retract
making it difficult to exit the vehicle or use the seat belt properly.
